KMuddy is a feature-rich MUD(Multi-User Dungeon) client for KDE.

Currently supported features include ANSI color, tabbed connection window,
MCCP v1/v2 compression, configurable colors and short-cuts, splitscreen
output history, command history, connection  profiles, intelligent
word-wrapping,  flexible  aliases and triggers with POSIX regular expressions,
session  transcripts,  macro  keys,  external  scripting, scripting variables,
Mud Sound Protocol, and more.

WWW:	http://www.kmuddy.com/
